-- AECOM Wins Contracts for Romanian Water, Sewage Projects
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2012-09-20T16:56:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-20/aecom-wins-contracts-for-romanian-water-sewage-projects.html
AECOM Technology Corp. (ACM) , a U.S.
engineering company, said it will provide technical assistance
to Romania’s water agency for three projects totaling at least
8.3 million euros ($11 million) in eastern  Europe .  The company was selected to assist on project management
services for the second phase of the Bucharest-Glina wastewater
treatment plant in Romania’s capital that’s valued at at least
7.1 million euros, according to an AECOM website  statement .  AECOM will also help upgrade the water system and sewer
network in the central city of Brasov for Compania de Apa Brasov
under a two-year contract.  The company will help the utility Apa Canal 2000 SA Pitesti
implement and monitor upgrades as well to the water and
wastewater system in Arges county in southern  Romania , it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  